⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of X
node PHN · PHN · ⟦X:PHN:61036f⟧

WHO   — X — a PHONETIKOS entry
WHAT  — X — the letter we reach for when we cannot name a thing: the unknown quantity, the unknown ray, the unmarked grave, the stolen name.
WHERE — Greek chi/xi to Roman ten to Descartes' algebra to the illiterate's mark to Malcolm X  Framework inputs: OED/etymonline; Cajori on math notation; Roentgen 1895; the Autobiography of Malcolm X; the standard account of the X-mark and its kiss  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — because a culture needs a single placeholder for 'here is something whose name we don't have,' and X — already the unknown of algebra and the mark of the nameless — became that placeholder everywhere
HOW   — one crossed shape pressed into service wherever a true name is missing — the variable, the ray, the spy, the buried spot, the unwritten signature, the stolen surname

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  X is the letter of the unknown and the unnamed; reach for it whenever the true name is missing.

